The article is a statement by the Vice President on the death of Nelson Mandela. The Vice President speaks highly of Mandela's wisdom, compassion, courage, and forgiveness, stating that he inspired and challenged us all to do better. The Vice President shares a personal experience of visiting South Africa and witnessing the racial segregation that Mandela fought against. He emphasizes that Mandela's courage and compassion transformed the world. The Vice President concludes by quoting an Irish poet and expressing that Mandela's presence made the world a better place.